<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000i and 9000i - RADIATOR, REMOVE AND REPLACE - RADIATOR AND
        COMPONENT REMOVal - RADIATOR SHROUD AND FRAME
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>RADIATOR SHROUD AND FRAME</title>
        <figure id="f1200820" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/g1200820.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 20. Radiator Frame Disassemble</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. CHARGE AIR COOLER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. RADIATOR CORE</callout1>
                <callout1>3. RADIATOR MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>4. RADIATOR FRAME</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>After locating and securing the radiator assembly in a safely supported position on the floor or work
            bench area, remove fan shroud and frame (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1200820">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove upper frame bolts.</para>
            <figure id="f1200821" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200821.webp" filename="../figg12/g1200821.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="272px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. Radiator Upper Frame Remove</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. UPPER RADIATOR FRAME BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CHARGE AIR COOLER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate, loosen and remove the charge air cooler mounting bolts from under surface of
                radiator cross frame.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the remainder of radiator frame bolts on each side of radiator. These
                bolts will also loosen the fan shroud assembly.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200822" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200822.webp" filename="../figg12/g1200822.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 22. Frame Removal (Passenger Side Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CHARGE AIR COOLER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. RADIATOR FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RADIATOR MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1200823" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200823.webp" filename="../figg12/g1200823.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 23. Radiator Fan Shroud Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RADIATOR SIDE FRAME</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
